getitdone
=========

Below are some usage examples.  Note that when arguments are quoted, it's
because the shell would interpret the special characters otherwise.

$ ./getitdone.py add Update 'periodic.conf(5)' and default/periodic.conf '#FreeBSD'
$ ./getitdone.py get
[  1]                    #FreeBSD Update periodic.conf(5) and default/periodic.conf
$ ./getitdone.py update 1 %90 
$ ./getitdone.py get
[  1]      90%           #FreeBSD Update periodic.conf(5) and default/periodic.conf
$ ./getitdone.py add Write example client code \#push2mob                                                                                                 
$ ./getitdone.py add Enhance with the newest featres \#push2mob
$ ./getitdone.py get \#push2mob
[  2]                    #push2mob Write example client code
[  3]                    #push2mob Enhance with the newest featres
